INSERT INTO `tblstories` VALUES (2,6,21,'The School Trip','It had been a boring school term. There had not been even a single notable event. However, one day our school head, Ms Mutize, made an announcement that brought excitement to the whole school. An educational tour was being organised for the end of the year.<p>\r\n\r\nThe plan was to go to Harare where we would visit some of the most exciting places in the city. Our \r\nparents were notified about the plan. They got SMS messages outlining the proposed dates for the trip \r\nand the payment required per child. A payment deadline was also set. This was meant to give the school sufficient time to hire the bus and buy the required materials.<p>\r\n\r\nI was overjoyed when I learnt that my parents had paid for me as soon as they had received the notice.\r\nThe number of paid students gradually increased as the payment deadline approached. At one point there \r\nwere fears that there might not be enough students funded for the trip. Such a situation would lead to\r\ncancellation of the trip which would cause great disappointment to those that had already paid. There \r\nwas, however, a boom in payments in the week leading to the payment deadline. We were thrilled when we heard this \r\nnews.<p>\r\n\r\nThe school administration then proceeded to hire the bus and book visiting times with all the organisations \r\nthat we had targeted to visit. These targeted sites included the National Museum, Robert Mugabe International Airport, \r\nand the Heroes Acre. We were all pleased with this selection. The school head finally announced that all \r\nthe preparations had been completed. After this announcement, time ticked slowly towards the date of departure. \r\n'),(2,6,22,'Rivers','Rivers are captivating natural features. They also have great significance as they influence the life patterns of both people and animals.<p>\r\n\r\nHuman settlement and habitation hinges on water availability so rivers naturally play an active role in this area. It is common for people to settle along a river course as this makes their survival and that of their livestock easy. Agricultural activities can be conveniently carried out when a river with a continuous flow of water exists nearby .<p>\r\n\r\nRivers can also be very useful as transport channels. Canoes and boats navigate various rivers around the world while transporting people and goods upstream or downstream as needed. River transport is, however,  not commonly used in some \r\ncountries due to some limitations. Firstly, natural features such as rapids and waterfalls make navigation hazardous.In addition, siltation also makes rivers impassable.<p>\r\n\r\nCountries also make grand plans that are supported by existing rivers. Industrial location is quite often \r\ndetermined by the courses of major rivers. The construction of dams across these rivers give them added significance and the benefits are automatically multiplied. Large fisheries that provide a lot of jobs are born. Food processing industries grow as a result.<p>\r\nIf rivers are not well maintained, however, they can be a serious danger to communities. Dumping industrial waste in rivers, for example, can cause death to animals and humans that come into contact with it. Biological waste in rivers \r\non the other hand leads to deadly diseases such as cholera and typhoid.'),(2,6,23,'The Gems of Zimbabwe','The Gems of Zimbabwe are the Zimbabwe senior national netball team. In the year 2019, the Gems brought happiness to a lot of Zimbabwean citizens by qualifying for the Netball World Cup.<p>\r\n\r\nThe tournament was hosted by England. All matches were played in the city of Liverpool. A total of sixteen \r\nteams were participating. Zimbabwe was one of the four African countries alongside Malawi, South Africa and Uganda. Four groups each comprising four teams were formed. The teams in each group were to play each other on a round robin \r\nbasis. The top three teams would proceed to play further matches which could earn them the title.\r\nThe bottom teams in each group, however, would be placed in their own group which would enable them to be ranked from 13th to 16th positions.<p>\r\n\r\nZimbabwe came second in their group of four. This achievement enabled them to advance to the next stage. They played very well and earned themselves great wins along the way. This was despite their height disadvantage as they had some of the shortest players at the tournament. The Gems eventually finished as number eight and were handsomely rewarded for their effort. The tournament was eventually won by New Zealand who defeated Australia in the final.<p>\r\n\r\nAs a result of their performance, the Zimbabwean Gems also won themselves a lot of supporters. After the tournament, some of the players managed to secure contracts with highly-ranked professional clubs. This has generated so much hope for the next tournament which is set to to be held in South Africa in 2023.\r\n\r\n'),(2,6,24,'The Ill Woman','Chipo sat on a stool looking at her frail mother who was lying on a straw mat. Tears began to soak in her eyes as \r\nshe stared pitifully at her only surviving parent. Chipo wished she could do something to help her ailing mother. She tried hard to devise a plan that could bring her mother back to normal health. However, \r\nat the back of her mind, she was convinced she was even more helpless than the patient.<p>\r\n\r\nTwo weeks earlier, her mother had begun complaining about weakness in her joints accompanied by a stupefying dizziness.\r\nSarah had suggested that she go to the clinic but her mother had rejected the idea. Instead, she had sent Sarah to call her elderly colleague who lived across the river. She had promptly responded to the call. She came and examined her junior \r\nfriend with such fervour that Sarah was momentarily convinced her mother would get well soon. Her mother was asked all \r\nkind of questions in order to determine the cause and subsequent cure for the illness. The elderly friend had gone back \r\nto her place and then returned with some herbs in a polythene bag.<p>\r\n\r\nSince that day, her mother had been restricted to only basic household tasks such as cooking and sweeping the hut and cooking meals. Fetching water and firewood had become Sarah\'s responsibilities as her mother was too weak to carry them out.\r\nHer health gradually deteriorated such that after a fortnight she could hardly move. Chipo then realised that feeling sorry for her \r\nmother and herself would not solve anything but would only worsen the situation. She watched her mother fall asleep. She \r\nthen quietly covered her with a light blanket before creeping out and closing the door.<p>\r\n\r\nShe had made up her mind to go and inform his uncle who stayed half a dozen kilometres away from their homestead. Her mother\'s illness was such a confusing matter for a child of her age. She had decided to act against her mother\'s will \r\nas she could not think about any solution on her own. The uncle would know better even though he and her sister were such fierce enemies.'),(2,6,25,'The Storm','Time was approaching mid afternoon and the sun shone brightly on the plain. We were taking care of our herd of cattle. It was in the middle of the summer. This meant that the movement of animals had to be controlled to protect the crops that were in the fields.<p>\r\n\r\nWe observed a heap of white fluffy clouds that was quickly building up on the eastern horizon. After a while, the mass of clouds turned into a deep grey colour. Sporadic flashes of lightning accompanied by thunder were seen. In no time, the rain  was \r\nupon us. It was accompanied by gusty winds which blew westwards. This had the undesired effect of driving the cattle in that direction. My colleagues and I tried to establish a wall to block them. The cattle were, however, too forceful for a mere three bodies and we were overpowered. The cattle drove us backwards until we were in a maize field.<p>\r\n\r\nAt this point, we realised there was no way we could push them back to the plain. Then it dawned on me that the western direction was actually the way home so we just drove the cattle in that direction, disregarding any crop fields in our way. We were fortunate that the wind maintained its direction which made it easy to drive the cattle. By the time we had reached home, \r\nwe had passed through half a dozen crop fields. There was serious damage to some of the crop but we could not help it.<p>\r\n\r\nWe quickly drove the cattle into the kraals and went home. We sat shivering by the fireside as we were drenched to the bone. Our goal for now, was to get warm. Tomorrow, would bring its new challenge of answering for our misdemeanour.'),(2,6,26,'Communal Work','The public dusty road had been severely damaged near Tsanga Bridge. Heavy rains had fallen the previous season and the river had broken its banks. As a result, a major section of the road had been eroded. Consequently, cars and small vans could not pass. Only buses and lorries could slowly negotiate the newly formed gullies and pass on.<p>\r\n\r\nVillagers got concerned as these developments caused them great inconvenience. The village leaders then called everyone for a meeting so that a solution could be found. It was agreed that the matter be reported to their district offices.\r\n\r\nUpon receiving the report, the District Administrator agreed to help the villagers. He, however, asked the villagers to help by performing some manual tasks as his office did not have sufficient labourers. The district office would provide the skilled workers to operate the machines and educate the villagers on safe working procedures.<p>\r\n\r\nAfter the visit, two weeks were allowed for work preparations and  educating the villagers. Smoking would be forbidden during work shifts to prevent fire outbreaks. In addition, the villagers were taught about the safety clothing that they \r\nwere to use and how they would put it on.<p>\r\n\r\nWhen the work finally started, the villagers worked with remarkable enthusiasm. They worked in teams on most of the tasks.\r\nGuidance was provided by the experienced district council workers. After a period of two weeks, the repairs were completed. The villagers were so delighted by the results of their work.'),(3,19,1,'Nzara','Achingoti mumba pori, Kudzai akabva ananga kuhuva kunova ndiko kwaiwanzogara pfuko yemaheu. Shungu dzake  dzaive dzekunyaradza nyoka dzemudumbu make dzaive dzorira. Akasvikosimudza mbiya \r\nyaive yakavhariswa pfuko achibva aridza tsamwa. Muhari maive mangosara magufu chete.<p>\r\n\r\nAkatanga kugwedebudza midziyo yese yemumba achivavarira kuwana chingamubatsire asi hapana chakabuda.\r\nAkabva abuda ndokutenderera kuseri kwemba uko kwaive nehozi. Akapinda muhozi akabva adongorera mudura maakange amboona nzungu svondo raive rapfuura asi musi uyu akatambirwa nemadziro chete.<p>\r\n\r\nAchiri kuedza kufunga rimwe zano, akabva anzwa mutsindo shure kwake ndokucheuka. Shamwari dzake Mufaro naKundai vaifamba vakabata bhora vakananga kubani uko vaiwanzotambira vachinge vabva kuchikoro. Achivaona, Kudzai akabva ati zvenzara pasi tsve, kwave kubatana navo vakananga kumutambo.'),(3,19,2,'Kudhibhu','Ndakapepuka nekugogodzwa kwakaitwa pamusuo wegota rangu. Semunhu aive arara akashonga kare, ndakamuka ndichibva ndati panze dhugu. Tapera aive amire pachivanze icho chiwepu chiri muruoko rwerudyi. Kuruboshwe aive nenduni yaive nemusoro mukuru sedamba. Kubuda kwandakaita hapana akataura nemumwe. Takadungamidzana takananga kudanga.<p> \r\n\r\nTapera ndiye akatanga kusvika ndokubvisa mahwere pamusuo kuti mombe dzibude. Mufambo wekuenda kudhibhu waive wakareba zvekuti taitofanira kukwitimisa mombe kuti tisvike zuva risati rabuda. Tyava dzakaridzwa kakuruva ndokuti mone tiri munzira yekudhibhu.NechekuMabvazuva utonga hwaive hwotsvuka saka paive pasisina nguva yekurasa.<p>\r\n\r\nTichiti vhu padhibhu, takawana mombe nevanhu zviri mavhu nemarara. Mudhibhisi aive amire nechemberi kunopinda nemombe mudhibhu achiongorora magwaro edanga regarega raive ropinda. Aisada kuti vanhu vasanganise matanga emombe sezvo zvaizomunetsa kupatsanura mombe dzacho padzaive dzodhibha. Isu takasvikomirawo nedanga redu kumucheto kwedzimwe tichimirira kuswederawo nekudhibha kwaiita dzakange dzatitangira kusvika.'),(3,19,3,'Africa','Africa idunhu guru rinobatanidza nyika dzakawanda. Ruzhinji rwenyika idzi rwunogara vanhu vechitema vanotaura mitauro yakasiyana-siyana yechizvarirwo chavo. Vachena vanowanikwawo mune dzimwe dzenyika idzi  kuburikidza nekupambwa kwaive kwakaitwa Africa nenyika dzekuEurope.  <p>\r\n\r\nNechekuMaodzanyemba ndiko kunowanikwa vanhu vechiArab vane ganda rakatoredzera revachena. Nyika dziri ikoko dzinosanganisira Egypt, Algeria, Morocco, Chad neTunisia. KuChamhembe kuzere vanhu vechitema avo vanowanikwa munyika dzinosanganisira Mozambique, Malawi, Zambia, Swaziland, South Africa, Lesotho, Botswana neZimbabwe. Pakati peAfrica nekuMavirira kwayo kune dzimwewo nyika dzakawandisa zvikuru zvekuti hatikwanise kudzidoma dzese panguva ino. <p>\r\n\r\nNyika ine vanhu vakawanda kupfuura dzese muAfrica iNigeria. Pane dzimwewo nyika dzine vanhu vakawanda zvikuru dzinoti Ethiopia, Egypt, DRC neSouth Africa. Zvizvarwa zveNigeria, Ethiopia neDRC zvakatekeshera nenyika dzakawanda dzemuAfrica nepasi rose. Izvi zvinonyanyokonzerwa nekutsvaga mikana yemabasa anopa goho guru.\r\n'),(3,19,4,'Mombe Mumunda','Takatinha mombe dzedu nemudeve merwizi Machena. Tyava dzairidzwa maungira achinzwika nechekuchikomo chaive kumhiri kwerwizi.<p>\r\n\r\nGwara ratakafamba naro zuva iri raive risiri iro remazuva ese. Kazhinji taisitenderera nekuseri kwegomo\r\nreMaranga tichizonoguma tave mubani raGwenhure munova ndimo mataifudzira mombe. Zuva iri takange tafunga zvekushandisa \r\ngwara rekudimbudzira raitevedza Machena. <p>\r\n\r\nMukufamba kwataiita takaerekana tadenha bumha renyuchi dzaive dzaungana pamuti weMusasa. Kuvhiringa kwatakadziita kwakadzipa \r\nhasha dzichibva dzatanga kuruma zvese mombe nevanhu. Rakava bararamhanya vanhu nemombe kuri kutiza hondo yenyuchi. Kana \r\nndiri seni ndakazonomira ndave mhiri kwaMachena. Kwandaive ndabva, Tonderai aive atove kure kwazvo achingomhanya \r\nchete pasina kucheuka. Ranganai ndiye wandakaona akwira pachuru chaive chinhambwe achiratidza kuti paaive amire paive \r\npachifura mhepo. <p>\r\n\r\nNdakadzosa maziso mudeve ndichiedza kuona kuti mombe dzaive dzimire papi wanike shomanana ndidzo dzaive dzakwidza naMachena.\r\nNdiri pakati pekuedza kunzwisisa kuti dzimwe dzese dzaivepi ndakanzwa izwi raidaidzira, \"Kumbirai, mombe mumunda!\" Ndichinzwa \r\nzita rangu ndakavhunduka ndichibva ndatarisa kwaibva izwi. Ndakamhanyira ikoko iyo hana ichingobika manhanga. Ndakapfuura nemukati mezvidenhe ndiri chahwiriri. Ndakazoerekana ndati pori mumunda mavaCharima wane mombe dziri mushishi kumweta chibage\r\nchevaridzi.Ndakanhonga mavhinga ndokudzikandidzira uku ndichibararadza kudaidza Ranganai. Ndaive ndisisazive pandaive ndarasira \r\nchiwepu zvekuti kutinha mombe dzacho kwaive kwatove kurima nechibhagera.'),(3,19,5,'Mabasa','\"Nhasi ngatikurukurei nezvemabasa atinoda kuzoita kana takura\". Uyu aive mudziidzisi \r\nChirenje wepachikoro cheKundai aitaura amire mberi kwevana vegwaro rechinomwe.<p>\r\n\r\n\"Ini ndinoda kuzovawo mudziidzisi semi\", Takudzwa akapindura. \"Ndinofadzwa zvikuru \r\nneruzivo rwamunotipakurira. Ndingafare kwazvo kana ndikazokwanisa kuitawo saizvozvo\r\nkana ndakura.\" Tapera akabva amugamha achiti, \"Ini zvangu ndinoda zvemabasa ekurima \r\nsezvinoita baba vangu. Gore regarega vanozadza matura zvekuti kumba kwedu hatizive \r\nchinonzi kusunza.\" Sekai akabva apindirawo achiti, \"Basa rehukoti ndiro randinofarira.\r\nGore rakapera baba vangu vakaenda kuchipatara vachirwara zvikuru asi mukoti akavarapa \r\nvakabva vanaya nenguva pfupipfupi.\"<p>\r\n\r\nRuzhinji rwevana rwakataura pamusoro pemabasa akasiyana siyana asi Revai naMunyaradzi\r\nvakaramba vakasona miromo. Mudziidzisi ndiye akazovadenha oti, \"Revai naMunyaradzi \r\ntiudzeiwo zvamunofunga\". \"Ini handione kukosha kwekushanda nekuti baba vangu vane mari zhinji. Zvese zvandinoda vanonditengera saka changu kudya ndirere zvangu\", akadaro Munyaradzi. \r\nAchipedza kutaura, mudziidzisi akabva amugamha achiti, \"Zvingadaro zvazvo asi zvakakosha kuti munhu \r\nwese agone kuzviriritira. Inozosvika nguva yekuti vabereki vedu vanenge votarisirawo\r\nkuchengetwa nesu. Regai tichinzwawo kureva kwaRevai.\" Vana vakabva vati bvu kuseka \r\nvanakidzwa. Uku Revai pfungwa dzaipishana sezvo aive asina kumbenge aizviisa mumusoro \r\nkuti angade kuzoita basa rei.<p>\r\n\r\nAchingoti simu pachigaro, dare rekupedza zvidziidzo zvemusi uyu rakabva ranzwika kurira.\r\nMudziidzisi akabva avhara zvidziidzo Revai ndokubuda muromo uchiita seuchasvika kunzeve.'),(3,19,6,'Nzvimbo Yechikoro','Shorai Mahere<br>\r\nChiroro School<br>\r\nP.O. Box 124<br>\r\nMvuma<p>\r\n\r\n12 Gunyana 2012<p>\r\n\r\nMukuru Wechikoro<br>\r\nChingwaru Secondary School<br>\r\nPrivate Bag 1022<br>\r\nGlendale<p>\r\n\r\nVanodiwa Mukuru Wechikoro  <p> \r\n\r\nRE: GWARO REKUTSVAGA NZVIMBO<p>\r\n\r\nNdanyora tsamba ino nechinangwa chekutsvaga nzvimbo yegwaro reForm 1 mugore rinouya.<p>\r\n\r\nNdiri mukomana ane makore gumi nemaviri ekuberekwa. Panguva ino ndiri kuita zvidziidzo zvegwaro rechinomwe pachikoro cheChiroro Primary. Ndinofarira zvidziidzo zvangu zvekare ndinoshanda nesimba zvekuti ndinotarisira kubudirira pabvunzo dzatichanyora pakupera kwegore.<p>\r\n\r\nNdingafare zvikuru ndikawana nzvimbo yekudziidza pachikoro penyu. Ndinotarisira mhinduro inofadza.<p>\r\n\r\nWenyu anovimbika<p>\r\n\r\n\r\nShorai Mahere\r\n\r\n');
